The Aratanha’s Farm is located at “Camocim de São Félix” (Pernambuco State, Brazil), approximately 25 miles west of Recife (the capital of the State), at 650m (2132 feet) of altitude, with cold climate (around 60°F in the Winter).The Aratanha’s Farm has 24 hectares (59,3 acres) and there we raise Alpine goats, Rhodesian Ridgeback dogs and some other animals, like the horse “Xodó” (Sweetheart) and the donkey “Filó”. It is a place of great natural beauties, where we already spent very happy moments!

PS: The Aratanha's Farm does not belong to me anymore.
